PART A: I request all records maintained by the U.S. Department of Education that show the following
information for each calendar day since September 1, 2023:
1. The total number of student loan borrowers who made a full payment on or before their
due date and the corresponding total value of those payments;
2. The total number of student loan borrowers who made a full payment after their due date
and the corresponding total value of those payments;
3. The total number of student loan borrowers who made a partial payment on or before
their due date and the corresponding total value of those payments;
4. The total number of student loan borrowers who made a partial payment after their due
date and the corresponding total value of those payments;
5. The total number of student loan borrowers who owed a payment but have not made any
payment since the payment pause ended;
6. The total number of borrowers enrolled in autopay at each servicer and the corresponding
total value of their loans;
7. The total number of student loan borrowers who made a payment under each of the
following repayment plans: standard, extended graduated, IBR, ICR, PAYE,
REPAYE/SAVE, alternative, income-sensitive, none; and the corresponding total values
of those payments;
8. The total number of federal student loan borrowers who are enrolled in each following
repayment plans: standard, extended graduated, IBR, ICR, PAYE, REPAYE/SAVE,
alternative, income-sensitive, none;
9. At each servicer, the total number of borrowers in each type of forbearance status (e.g.,
mandatory, administrative, etc);
10. At each servicer, the total number of borrowers in each type of deferment status;
11. The total number of federal student loan borrowers who owe a $0 monthly payment
under any income-driven repayment plan;
12. The total number of federal student loan borrowers who are 0-7 days delinquent;
13. The total number of federal student loan borrowers who are 8-14 days delinquent;
14. The total number of federal student loan borrowers 15-30 days delinquent;
15. The total number of federal student loan borrowers who are 31-59 days delinquent;
16. The total number of borrower who are 60-90 days delinquent; and
17. The total number of borrowers who are more than 90 days delinquent.
